Canadian Currency Trading Rises 5.9% a Day in April

-- B y   C h r i s   F o u r n i e r
-- 
2011-07-25T15:53:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/canadian-currency-trading-rises-5-9-to-1-2-trillion-a-day.html
(Corrects amount in the first paragraph.)  Canadian currency turnover rose to
an average $61.2 billion a day in April, an increase of 5.9
percent from October, according to a semi-annual survey of
trading published by the Canadian Foreign Exchange Committee.  To contact the reporter on this story:
